:       \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-06-profile-capabilities-verification\",\n2420:       \"sourceBehavior\": \"`Profile.kt` renders a back command, static profile action cards, and a logout button. The back arrow calls `navController.navigateUp()`, the action cards keep placeholder click handlers, and logout clears the start destination stack before routing to onboarding.\",\n2421:       \"targetBehavior\": \"`profile_route_service.cj` now centralizes the profile-specific back-route decision, explicit edit/section placeholder action messages, and logout transition state, while `renderProfileRoute` preserves the visible back affordance, static action cards, and logout button. `bootstrap_page.cj` delegates the profile logout flow and typed profile action callbacks to the focused profile transition/service endpoints before routing to onboarding after session logout.\",\n2422:       \"verificationEvidence\": [\n2423:         \"Manual source review confirmed `Profile.kt` owns the back icon, edit/action-card click surfaces, and logout navigation callback.\",\n2424:         \"Manual target review confirmed `profile_route_service.cj::resolveBackRoute`, `::canNavigateBack`, `::buildLogoutTransition`, `::editActionMessage`, and `::sectionActionMessage` now carry the profile-specific command wiring instead of closing the row through only the broad bootstrap shell.\",\n2425:         \"`profile_page.cj::buildProfileTopBar`, `::buildProfileSection`, and `::renderProfileRoute` preserve the visible back/logout/action-card surface while `profile_store.cj::logoutRoute`, `::actionFeedbackMessage`, and `::sectionFeedbackMessage` keep the route/message state explicit.\",\n2426:         \"Final-coverage test build report PASS: `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/final-coverage/test-build-report.md` ran `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` from `entry/src/test/cangjie` successfully.\",\n2427:         \"Phase-06 build gate PASS: `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-06-profile-capabi